    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="356"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d356">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115/6182</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 1, 1915</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 2, 12.35 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3170. My 3149, November 23.<note n="1" xml:id="d356fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    Foreign Office grants definite export permission for shipment 15,000 <hi
                        rend="italic">Zentner</hi> sugar-beet seed to be consigned Secretary
                    Agriculture and distributed, delivery as follows: Zuckerfabrik, Kleinwanzleben,
                    5,600; Heinrich Mette, Quedlinburg, 1,200; Dippe Brothers, Quedlinburg, 2,200;
                    C. Braune, Bernburg, 1,800; Schreiber and Son, Nordhausen, 3,000; Heine,
                    Hadmersleben, 1,200 <hi rend="italic">Zentner</hi>.</p>
                <p>Department’s 2437, November 24.<note n="1" xml:id="d356fn2">Not printed.</note>
                    German Government regrets to be unable allow further exportations beet seed
                    without equivalent and refers to reasons transmitted in my 3075, November 3.
                    Your 2424, November 20.<note n="1" xml:id="d356fn3">Not printed.</note> No
                    objection on part German Government to transshipment of beet seed released in
                    Austria-Hungary as not forbidden. Have communicated with Consul Donegan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
